dc_description_s: This data layer represents significant facility locations for Walworth County, Wisconsin in 2016. It is a feature class within the geodatabase 'Walworth_Parks_2016.gdb'. [Points that represent significant facility locations in a community. Examples include schools, government facilities, stadiums, casinos, and fire stations. In some cases, there may be multiple FacilitySitePoints for a single FacilitySite polygon. Additional information about each Facility can be organized in to separate tables and related to these locations using the FacilityID key. The feature classification and type schema for the facility sites grew out of work with the Department of Homeland Security's HSIP Program and has evolved to support a diverse set of facilities inventoried for a variety of uses by a local government.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For the most current data for this county, please visit: https://open-walco.opendata.arcgis.com/
